futureArrival

public void futureArrival(Job f,
                          double arrivesAt)
The machine is notified of the future arrival of the job f at a certain time. Note that f is not the job itself but a clone of this job with current operation advanced to this machine obtained with j.getFuture().

numJobsWaiting

public int numJobsWaiting()
Return the number of jobs waiting in queue, ready to be started immediately. This does not include the KeepIdleDummy. This means, the following equation holds: queue.size()==numJobsWaiting()+ numFutures()+1.

See Also:
